title: Mocs Nip Wofford, Stay Unbeaten In SoCon
text:
Saturday, October 24 2015, 11:45 PM EDT Mocs Nip Wofford, Stay Unbeaten In SoCon Enrique Ribiero booted a 38-yard field goal as time expired, lifting the Chattanooga Mocs to a 20-17 win over Wofford Saturday in Spartanburg, South Carolina. The winning kick came after the Terriers tied the game up with less than three minutes to play. Derrick Craine rushed for 90 yards and a touchdown to lead the UTC offensive attack. It's Chattanooga's first win at Wofford since 1998. UTC will host Western Carolina next weekend. It's Homecoming week for Chattanooga.
